Filters:
    - filters are used to format the data accroding to application requirement.

    - we have two types of filters.

        1. predefined filters

        2. custom filters

predefined filters:
    - the filters given by the framework called as predefined filters.

1. uppercase

    - this filter used to convert the lower case characters to uppercase.

Ex.
    {{'hello'}} //hello
    {{'hello' | uppercase }} //HELLO


2. lowercase

    - this filter used to convert the uppercase characters to lowercase.

Ex.
    {{"HELLO"}} //HELLO
    {{"HELLO" | lowercase}} //hello


3. currency

    - this filter used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical values.

Ex.
    {{100}}  //100
    {{100 | currency}} //$100.00
    {{100 | currency:"$":4}}  //$100.0000


4. orderBy

    - this filter used to arrange the data either in assending / decending order.


5. limitTo

    - this filter used to display the number of records from an array.


6. filter

    - this filter used to search the whole array based on user input.

Ex.
    $scope.my_array = [{'id':1,'sub':'AngularJS'},
                        {'id':5,'sub':'MongoDB'},
                        {'id':2,'sub':'Angular4'},
                        {'id':4,'sub':'NodeJS'},
                        {'id':3,'sub':'reactJS'}];

    <input type = "text" ng-model="search"> <br><br>
    <table border="1">
        <tr>
            <th>id</th>
            <th>sub</th>
        </tr>
        <tr ng-repeat="x in my_array | orderBy:'id' | limitTo:3 | filter: search">
            <td>{{x.id}}</td>
            <td>{{x.sub}}</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

7. date
    - this filter used to format the date accroding to application requirement.

Ex.

    {{new Date() | date:'dd-MM-yy'}}
    {{new Date() | date:'MM-dd-yyyy'}}
    {{new Date() | date:'shortDate'}}
    {{new Date() | date:'medium'}}
    {{new Date() | date:'fullDate'}}
    {{new Date() | date:'shortTime'}}


8. json
    - this filter used to convert the json objects to json strings.








